        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 10:06PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1006 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Point Comfort, or 11 miles northeast of Port Lavaca, moving northeast
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Palacios, La Ward, and Lolita.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
